027/**
028 * Top-level ATOM feed object.
029 *
030 * <p>
031 * Represents an <c>atomFeed</c> construct in the RFC4287 specification.
032 *
033 * <h5 class='figure'>Schema</h5>
034 * <p class='bschema'>
035 *    atomFeed =
036 *       element atom:feed {
037 *          atomCommonAttributes,
038 *          (atomAuthor*
039 *           &amp; atomCategory*
040 *           &amp; atomContributor*
041 *           &amp; atomGenerator?
042 *           &amp; atomIcon?
043 *           &amp; atomId
044 *           &amp; atomLink*
045 *           &amp; atomLogo?
046 *           &amp; atomRights?
047 *           &amp; atomSubtitle?
048 *           &amp; atomTitle
049 *           &amp; atomUpdated
050 *           &amp; extensionElement*),
051 *          atomEntry*
052 *       }
053 * </p>
054 *
055 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
056 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanAtom">juneau-bean-atom</a>
057 * </ul>
058 */
059@Bean(typeName="feed")
060@FluentSetters
061public class Feed extends CommonEntry {
062
063   private Generator generator;  // atomGenerator?
064   private Icon icon;            // atomIcon?
065   private Logo logo;            // atomLogo?
066   private Text subtitle;        // atomSubtitle?
067   private Entry[] entries;      // atomEntry*
068
069   /**
070    * Normal constructor.
071    *
072    * @param id The feed identifier.
073    * @param title The feed title.
074    * @param updated The feed updated timestamp.
075    */
076   public Feed(Id id, Text title, Calendar updated) {
077      super(id, title, updated);
078   }
079
080   /**
081    * Normal constructor.
082    *
083    * @param id The feed identifier.
084    * @param title The feed title.
085    * @param updated The feed updated timestamp.
086    */
087   public Feed(String id, String title, String updated) {
088      super(id, title, updated);
089   }
090
091   /** Bean constructor. */
092   public Feed() {}
093
094

227   /**

253      return this;
254   }
